This article summarizes a meeting between Vice President Kamala Harris and President Hakainde Hichilema of Zambia at the White House. Vice President Harris welcomes President Hichilema and highlights the significance of his visit, as it is the first time Zambia has been welcomed to the White House since 1992. They discuss the shared commitment to democracy and the importance of respecting the rule of law. They also talk about their partnership in addressing global health and the environment, particularly in mitigating the effects of the climate crisis and investing in renewable energies. Both leaders emphasize the interconnectedness and interdependence of nations in facing challenges such as pandemics and climate change. President Hichilema congratulates Vice President Harris on her election win and expresses gratitude for the invitation to the White House. They agree on the importance of valuing democracy, the rule of law, and institutionalism in delivering economic growth and development for their respective countries. President Hichilema mentions the establishment of a Ministry of Green Economy and Environment in Zambia to address climate change issues. Both leaders express alignment in their values and vision.